| [Client LoCs](#client-locs) | `ClientLoCs` | The level of confidence your service requests. The value is a string such as `P0`, `P1` or `P2`. |
| [Client name (Service name)](#client-name) | `ClientName` | The name of your service, visible to users in the sign in journey. |
| [Client secret](#client-secret) | `ClientSecret` | The client secret used to validate `/token` requests. Only used if the token authentication method is `client_secret_post`. |
| Client type* | `ClientType` | Internal use only. The value is always `web`. |
| [Contacts](#contacts) | `Contacts` | Email addresses of your service's technical contacts. |
| Cookie consent shared* | `CookieConsentShared` | Internal use only. The value is always `false`. |
| [ID token signing algorithm](#id-token-signing-algorithm) | `IdTokenSigningAlgorithm` | Either `RS256` or `ES256`. Defaults to `ES256`. |
| [Identity verification supported](#identity-verification-supported) | `IdentityVerificationSupported` | Whether your service uses identity verification. |
| Is active* | `IsActive` | Internal use only. |
| [JAR validation required](#jar-validation-required) | `JarValidationRequired` | Whether your service must send a signed JSON Web Token (JWT) authorisation request (JAR). |
